      • createNode

        protected static Node createNode(Network network,
                                 org.json.JSONObject jsonNode)
                          throws NodeException,
                                 org.json.JSONException
        Factory method to create a Node for use by the Network class.
        Creates the underlying logic objects.
        Note: loading tables will fail if parent nodes do not exist in the model. In that case load all nodes first without tables and then use setTable(JSONObject) after all nodes, states, intra and cross network links had been created.
        Parameters:
        network - Network that the Node will be added to
        jsonNode - configuration of the Node
        Returns:
        created Node
        Throws:
        NodeException - if failed to create the node
        org.json.JSONException - if JSON configuration is incomplete or invalid
        See Also:
        setTable(JSONObject)

                                 org.json.JSONObject jsonNode,
                                 boolean withTables)
                          throws NodeException,
                                 org.json.JSONException
        Factory method to create a Node for use by the Network class.
        Creates the underlying logic objects.
        Note: loading tables will fail if parent nodes do not exist in the model. In that case load all nodes first without tables and then use setTable(JSONObject) after all nodes, states, intra and cross network links had been created.
        Parameters:
        network - Network that the Node will be added to
        jsonNode - configuration of the Node
        withTables - whether to load node tables from JSON
        Returns:

      • setTable

        public void setTable(org.json.JSONObject jsonTable)
              throws NodeException
        Replaces the Node's probability table with one specified in the given JSON.
        This must be used after all parents states and incoming links had been created.
        Parameters:
        jsonTable - configuration of the table in JSON format
        Throws:
        NodeException - if:
        ∙ table type does not match the rest of the table configuration
        ∙ table is not a square matrix
        ∙ the number of cells does not match the number of partitions created by the combination of parent states

      • setTableFunction

        public void setTableFunction(String expression)
                      throws NodeException
        Sets Node function to the one provided. Will use node parent IDs and expression variables as allowed tokens.
        Resets Node table partitioning and sets Table type to NodeConfiguration.TableType.Expression.
        Parameters:
        expression - function to set
        Throws:
        NodeException - if function is invalid

      • setTableFunction

        public void setTableFunction(String expression,
                             List<String> allowedTokens)

        Sets Node function to the one provided.
        Resets Node table partitioning and sets Table type to NodeConfiguration.TableType.Expression.
        Parameters:

        Throws:

      • setTableFunction

        public void setTableFunction(String expression,
                             List<String> allowedTokens,
                             boolean relaxFunctionRequirements)
                      throws NodeException
        Sets Node function to the one provided.
        Resets Node table partitioning and sets Table type to NodeConfiguration.TableType.Expression.
        Parameters:
        expression - function to set
        allowedTokens - list of parent IDs, variable names etc to add as parseable tokens; if null, all tokens are allowed
        relaxFunctionRequirements - if true, all function requirements are lifted and any number of arguments are allowed
        Throws:
        NodeException - if function is invalid

      • setTableFunctions

        public void setTableFunctions(String[] functions)
                       throws NodeException
        Sets Node functions to the ones provided.
        Also sets Table type to NodeConfiguration.TableType.Partitioned.
        If the node only has one non-simulated parent, this parent will be automatically used to partition this node.
        Parameters:
        functions - functions to set
        Throws:
        NodeException - if a function is invalid

        Parameters:

        Throws:

      • convertToSimulated

        public boolean convertToSimulated()
                           throws NodeException
        Enables calculation simulation for the Node (only possible for ContinuousInterval or IntegerInterval nodes).
        All current states will be replaced by dynamic states.
        Returns:
        true if action was performed, false if no action was permitted or required
        Throws:
        NodeException

      • convertToStatic

        public boolean convertToStatic(DataSet dataSet)
                        throws NodeException
        Disables simulation and converts dynamic states from the results of the provided DataSet into static permanent states.
        Any VariableObservations in the DataSet will replace current Node variable defaults and will be replaced from the DataSet observations.
        Parameters:
        dataSet - DataSet to use for creating static states from results
        Returns:
        true if action was performed, false if no action was permitted or required
        Throws:
        NodeException - if states could not be created from the DataSet results
